---
import DocLayout from '../layouts/DocLayout.astro';
import Callout from '../components/Callout.astro';
import PersonaCard from '../components/PersonaCard.astro';
import ResourceCard from '../components/ResourceCard.astro';
import LayerBadge from '../components/LayerBadge.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<DocLayout
  title="VISDOM Code Review"
  subtitle="A multi-layered, AI-driven code review framework for enterprise teams. Safety net for AI-generated code."
  tags={[
    { label: "VISDOM", variant: "green" },
    { label: "Code Review", variant: "gray" },
    { label: "Enterprise", variant: "outline" },
  ]}
  next={{ label: "Architecture", href: `${base}architecture/` }}
>

<h2>What It Is</h2>

<p>
  VISDOM Code Review (VCR) is a <strong>multi-layered, AI-driven code review framework</strong> for enterprise teams.
  It provides structured, automated review of pull requests — from deterministic static analysis through
  AI-powered deep review — and proactive repository-wide quality scanning.
</p>

<p>
  VCR is part of the <a href="https://virtuslab.com/services/visdom">VISDOM</a> Agent-Ready SDLC offering,
  sitting within the <strong>Automated Risk Assessment</strong> pillar alongside Context Fabric and Machine-Speed CI.
</p>

<p>
  The framework is <strong>process-first and technology-agnostic</strong>. It defines what to check, when, and how deep —
  not which specific tools to use. Reference implementations are provided for GitHub + GitHub Actions,
  with the process portable to any platform.
</p>

<h2>The Problem</h2>

<p>Enterprise teams want to deploy AI-generated code but lack a safety net. Four pain points converge:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Senior bottleneck</strong> — seniors spend 30-50% of time reviewing junior/mid code</li>
  <li><strong>Inconsistent quality</strong> — distributed teams (PL/UK/IN) apply different review standards</li>
  <li><strong>Slow feedback loop</strong> — PRs wait 24-48h for review due to timezone gaps</li>
  <li><strong>AI-code trust gap</strong> — teams are afraid to ship AI-generated code because existing CI is a lying oracle</li>
</ul>

<Callout type="warning" title="The Lying Oracle">
  <p>
    CI pipelines treat test results as ground truth, but flaky tests lie intermittently
    (Google: 84% of pass-to-fail transitions are flaky) and AI-generated tests lie systematically
    (Circular Test Trap — tests verify what code <em>does</em>, not what it <em>should do</em>).
    VCR addresses both failure modes.
  </p>
  <p>
    Read more: <a href="https://virtuslab.com/blog/ai/the-fallacy">The Agent-Ready SDLC, Post #3</a>
  </p>
</Callout>

<h2>How It Works</h2>

<p>Every PR passes through layers of increasing depth and cost:</p>

<div class="flex flex-col gap-3 my-6">
  <a href={`${base}layers/context-collection/`} class="block border border-visdom-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow no-underline">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-1">
      <LayerBadge layer={0} />
      <span class="text-xs text-visdom-gray-400">&lt;10s</span>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-visdom-gray-600 !mb-0">Deterministic context gathering from repository knowledge, git data, and test reliability history.</p>
  </a>

  <a href={`${base}layers/deterministic-gate/`} class="block border border-visdom-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow no-underline">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-1">
      <LayerBadge layer={1} />
      <span class="text-xs text-visdom-gray-400">&lt;60s</span>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-visdom-gray-600 !mb-0">Zero AI. Linters, SAST, secret scan, coverage delta. 100% repeatable. Cannot be prompt-injected.</p>
  </a>

  <a href={`${base}layers/ai-quick-scan/`} class="block border border-visdom-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow no-underline">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-1">
      <LayerBadge layer={2} />
      <span class="text-xs text-visdom-gray-400">&lt;2 min</span>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-visdom-gray-600 !mb-0">Fast AI pass over diff. Risk classification (LOW→CRITICAL). Quick findings (max 5). AI-code detection.</p>
  </a>

  <a href={`${base}layers/ai-deep-review/`} class="block border border-visdom-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow no-underline">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-1">
      <LayerBadge layer={3} />
      <span class="text-xs text-visdom-gray-400">&lt;10 min · MEDIUM+ risk only</span>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-visdom-gray-600 !mb-0">Full analysis with repo context, history, conventions. Multiple Review Lenses in parallel.</p>
  </a>
</div>

<Callout type="tip" title="Layered cost model">
  <p>
    LOW-risk PRs complete in under 2 minutes at ~$0.05. Only MEDIUM+ risk triggers the expensive Layer 3.
    This is how VCR scales to hundreds of PRs/day without cost explosion.
  </p>
</Callout>

<h2>Design Principles</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Process-first, tool-agnostic</strong> — defines steps, inputs, outputs, quality gates. Reference implementations are provided; the process is portable.</li>
  <li><strong>Layered depth</strong> — review depth scales with risk. Cheap and fast for trivial PRs, thorough for critical ones.</li>
  <li><strong>Opinionated defaults, full flexibility</strong> — ships with "VISDOM Standard" review categories. Clients can add, remove, or replace.</li>
  <li><strong>Deterministic backstop</strong> — Layer 1 cannot be fooled by prompt injection, hallucination, or non-determinism. It is the floor.</li>
  <li><strong>Precision over recall</strong> — better to miss a LOW finding than report a false positive. Silence is OK.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Deliverable Model</h2>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Component</th>
      <th>What you get</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Framework</strong></td>
      <td>Process definition, configuration schema, prompt templates, reference implementation</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Pilot deployment</strong></td>
      <td>Working pipeline on 1-2 client teams, configured for their stack</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Knowledge transfer</strong></td>
      <td>Client team owns and operates VCR after engagement</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><strong>Reference platform</strong></td>
      <td>GitHub + GitHub Actions (first). Other platforms follow the same process.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>How Different Roles See It</h2>

<PersonaCard name="Katja" role="Engineering Manager" color="green">
  <p>"My seniors spend half their time reviewing junior PRs from our India team. VCR gives them back that time — the AI catches the obvious stuff, and reviewers only focus on what the PR comment highlights."</p>
  <p><strong>What Katja should do</strong> — measure senior review time before/after pilot. Track comment engagement rate.</p>
</PersonaCard>

<PersonaCard name="Rajesh" role="Senior Developer" color="blue">
  <p>"I was skeptical about AI reviewing my code, but the risk classifier is smart — it doesn't bother me with LOW-risk PRs. And the AI-Code Safety lens caught a hallucinated API I missed in a Copilot-generated PR."</p>
  <p><strong>What Rajesh should do</strong> — customize <code>.vcr/conventions.md</code> with team-specific patterns. Add custom lenses for domain rules.</p>
</PersonaCard>

<PersonaCard name="Ewa" role="Platform Engineer" color="purple">
  <p>"The TORS filtering alone was worth it. Our agents were burning $30 on flaky test loops. Now they get clean signals and converge in 3 iterations instead of 47."</p>
  <p><strong>What Ewa should do</strong> — integrate VCR metrics (ITS, CPI, TORS) into the team dashboard. Set budget caps.</p>
</PersonaCard>

<PersonaCard name="Marcus" role="CFO" color="amber">
  <p>"I approved 50 Copilot licenses at $950/month. Nobody told me the real cost was $17,000. VCR's dashboard finally gave me visibility into the 4x hidden tax."</p>
  <p><strong>What Marcus should do</strong> — review the <a href={`${base}metrics/`}>Metrics Framework</a> and the 4x Hidden Tax breakdown.</p>
</PersonaCard>

<h2>Further Reading</h2>

<div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-3 mb-8">
  <ResourceCard
